race.comment: CRAVING MAGIC (9) tackled open company and got the job done with a tenacious win over 1300m at Canberra last start. Won't find this any harder and in a very open affair looks a strong chance with a nice run assured out of the good barrier. ARTFUL PERSUASION (7) produced an eye-catcher two back over the mile at this track then started favourite in town but wasn't quite up to it. Has a fine record here at this distance and with the winkers back on should run a huge race. CHEEKY DANCER (10) has been safely held in her two runs this time in work. Looking for this extra trip now, the blinkers are back on, and Fitzgerald's claim brings her in beautifully. Everything points to a much better run today. COMMANDING ARTIST (8) has been going okay in town of late although the mile at Warwick Farm last time was a bit too much. Big chance back at the provincials over today's journey. TITANIUM MISS (6) appreciated the step up to 1400m last start when successful at Warwick Farm. In the mix again.
